Review Comment:
   Sorry for bringing back this point, something feel not right so I checked a bit more. Under the hood, StringToDecimal uses a custom parser:
   [decimal.cc#L511](https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/cpp/src/arrow/util/decimal.cc#L511) -> [decimal.cc#L450](https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/cpp/src/arrow/util/decimal.cc#L450) -> [decimal.cc#L467](https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/cpp/src/arrow/util/decimal.cc#L467)
   It is independent of the std::locale. This test block (line 1936->1941) is kind of redundant.

